---
title: Build-Your-Own Burger Bar One recipe—endless ways to enjoy!
description: How do you make everyone happy at dinnertime? A DIY burger bar! Keep it simple with sliced cheddar and ketchup tucked into a pillowy brioche bun; or go all out with tomato, pickles, lettuce, crispy fried onions, and mayo (plus potato wedges on the side). Order extras like bacon or add sweet potatoes for another side option!

image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/669ecf5546ae2b14647c3c9f-8c35c925.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/669ecf5546ae2b14647c3c9f-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/build-your-own-burger-bar-669ecf5546ae2b14647c3c9f
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
author: Sara Heilman
servings: 2
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 1140 kcal
  fat: 65 g
  saturated fat: 22 g
  carbohydrates: 88 g
  sugar: 20 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1910 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Cut @Russet Potato{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges.

Toss potato on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender,
~{20-25%minutes}.

> TIP: If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert),
> you can get started on them now!

Meanwhile, trim and discard root end from @Baby Lettuce{1}; separate leaves. Set
larger leaves aside; finely slice remaining leaves crosswise. Thinly slice
@Tomato{1} into rounds; transfer to a #plate{} and season all over with @salt and
@pepper.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @Ground Beef{10%ounce}, @Beef Stock Concentrate{1},
@Onion Powder{1%tablespoon}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and @pepper{}.

> 3/4 tsp salt for 4 servings.

Form into two patties (four patties for 4), each slightly wider than a burger
bun.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add patties
(depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches) and cook to
desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side (reduce heat to medium and cover if
patties begin to brown too quickly).

> TIP: To make cheeseburgers, in the last 1-2 minutes of cooking top patties with
> cheddar; cover pan to melt cheese.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

While patties cook, halve and toast @Brioche Buns{2}; transfer to a
#serving platter{}.

> TIP: Begin setting up your burger bar with toppings if potato wedges and
> patties are still cooking!

Serve lettuce leaves, shredded lettuce, tomato, patties, buns,
@Dill Pickle{1}(sliced), @Crispy Fried Onions{1%ounce}, @Ketchup{1}, @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon},
and any remaining @Cheddar Cheese{2%slice} family style and let everyone build
their own burgers.

Serve with potato wedges on the side.